entries.femaleVariant: So, what? I dust off and load up my Tsunami? Rejoin your crusade against Arasaka?
Bingo.
When?
Dunno... Now?
Hmm. And what makes you think I'd agree?
You owe me one.
'Cause I think you know you owe me one.
That's where you come in.
Need people and gear.
You're the best fixer in town.
You tell me how we're gonna do this.
We need bodies. You know the kind.
And we need gear. Best money can buy.
And some luck. Hopefully a little fuckin' luck.
Fuck plans! When have they ever helped us?
Oh, Christ. See, that's what's wrong with kids these days. Everybody's always askin' about some fuckin' plan.
You owe it to yourself.
Did you say "we"?
Can't possibly do it without you.
Really wanna miss out on a chance like this?
That's right. Can't possibly work without you.
Willin' to miss out on this?
It ever been different?
Back in the day, you snorted some lines, grabbed your iron and did what needed doin'. And that's why it worked.
And it'll work for us now.
V's dying. She needs my help.
entries.maleVariant: V's dying. He needs my help.

entries.femaleVariant: This body... I'm trying to... I'm not... Fuck!
V's dying and I'm the fuckin' cancer killin' 'er.
entries.maleVariant: V's dying and I'm the fuckin' cancer killin' 'im.

entries.femaleVariant: But the process can be stopped. I just have to--
No, Johnny. Don't start.
Don't tell yourself you're out to help someone. It's only ever about you – so you can feel better.
Oh, fuck off, princess.
Oh, fuck off, princess.
Need to get into 'Saka Tower.
I've changed.
Jesus, who died?
Not happy to see me?
Frankly, I'm not sure.
Why? We had fun at the movies, didn't we?
You want something. And that's always a bad sign.
Plus, got a good idea why you're here.
I'm runnin' out of time, Rogue.
When that fuckin' clock strikes twelve, Johnny'll disappear, and V'll go with him.
Need to get myself outta her head before that happens.
entries.maleVariant: Need to get myself out of his head before that happens.

entries.femaleVariant: We managed to contact Alt. She agreed to help.
But?
Only one place we can do it – a data fort, Mikoshi.
Only an idiot does the same thing over and over while expecting things to work out differently.
You even have a plan for this?
Some things never change.
I dunno.
Shit. Knew this would happen one day.
Well, whaddaya say we go find out.
Will ya lend me a hand?
Shut the fuck up, Johnny…
'Course I do.
Pretty nice setup, Rogue.
Pretty tight setup you got, Rogue.
Couldn't've been easy to achieve all this. So many others failed.
[Sit] V's on a break. It's me.
Out of that whole crazy crew from Atlantis, by some crazy coincidence, only you survived.
We're not at the movies anymore.
Hey everybody! We're closed! Now.
Whoa. What gives? We ain't finished yet!
Oh yes you is!
Sheesh, what's the matter?
Nothin'. You're shift's done. You're headin' home to kick your feet up.
We’ll have the whole place to ourselves? Hmm, VIP treatment!
Now talk. Just what the hell are you insinuating?
Just thinking back. You ever miss the old days?
Ya miss the old times at all, Rogue?
Fine with where they are, fine with where I am.
Shame no one else from the Atlantis had the same luck.
Just trying to fill in some gaps.
Somehow missed the last fifty years. Just tryin' to get my facts straight, fill in some gaps.
And? You learn anything useful?
Just that no one from our old crew got a happy ending.
No one but you.
Just thinkin' back.
[Sit] You chose a cozy life. Just curious what it cost you.
[Sit] Let's see your cards. 'Cause I think you sold out to the corps.
Listen, Rogue, just show me your hand. I know you sold out.
You think I sold-- You fucking prick!
I saved what was left of the Atlantis. What you hadn't managed to destroy!
Not insinuating anything. Just a little curious.
Chose a cozy life for yourself. I'm just curious what it cost you.
I can see that.
The hell's that s'posed to mean?
That's right. But that's not why you're here.
Are you serious? Arasaka, again?!
Jesus, Johnny... You're obsessed!
Now, no reason to get angry... The past is the past.
Right, so we know of an access point to Mikoshi. It's under Arasaka Tower.
That's where I need to get to.
It's where I'll port Alt into the system.
Which is the only way V and I can... part ways.
Not OK just staying in that body?
It's gotten a little tight.
Fuck Arasaka! This is about V.
I see it more as a hobby.
Fuck Arasaka! This is about V.
I see it more as a hobby.
Well, maybe I've changed.
[Sit] Guess again.
Owe it to yourself.
I'll put it to you this way, Wakako – don't get in my way.
You're running your little operation only because I have allowed it. And I can change my mind whenever I want.
Hang on, gimme a sec.
V?
V's takin' a break. It's me.
Try again, Rogue. Got one more guess.
Johnny.
We'll talk soon, Wakako.
Whaddaya want, Johnny?
Expected a smile, at least.
Interrupted important biz, did I?
Interrupted important biz, did I?
Got a strange feeling this conversation could be more important.
If I hadn't, you'd've dragged me down with you.
We all pay a price for the choices we make. I'm no exception.
You wanna drag me into something again. And this chatter is just a prelude.
Need to get into 'Saka Tower, and you're gonna help me do that.
This body is dying. And I'm the cancer killing it.
entries.maleVariant: This body is dying. And I'm the cancer killin' it.

entries.femaleVariant: Me and everybody else you buried while you climbed to the top.
Is that so?
Sure, you can just be the queen of the ball in Night City, but that's not the real Rogue.
Look deep. I know you can find her again.
Arasaka? Again? Shoulda seen that coming.
[Sit]
[Stand]
Hang on. "Us?"
And us? Have we changed?
Just... stop talking.
And the only access point we got a chance of reachin' is tucked snugly under 'Saka Tower.
The real Rogue you buried while you climbed to the top.
You want something. And that's always a bad sign.
'Course I do.
And who better could I take it to?
Queen of Night City.
That one night, by some fucking miracle, you'd waltz in here and tear everything down.
Did you put everyone on the corp chopping block or just me?
Just you.
Like you did the rest.
That what you tell yourself when you're cashin' corp checks?
That's what I tell myself when I stand over the graves of the crew from the Atlantis.
It's what I tell myself when I look at you now.
Well, hey... the past is the past.
Well, hey... the past is the past.
entries.maleVariant: Well, hey... the past... is the past.

entries.femaleVariant: Hey there, V. Drop in for one last drink before turnin' in?
Lookin' for Rogue.
I'm lookin' for Rogue.
Last? I'm just gettin' started.
Big booth over there. But you probably don't wanna disturb her now.
No, I think I do.
Last? I'm just gettin' started.
Wait, no, I'm serious! She'll kick ya in the can!
That what you think? Then just watch and learn.
Oh, I'll watch... but I doubt I'll be the one to get a lesson.
Oh, too bad, we're closin' up.
Tellin' ya, I saw 'em in Salvador. Fuckin' killin' machines.
Is that my bottle? Behind the bar?
That my bottle behind the bar?
Yep. Been waitin' there. Just… I never knew what the fuck for.
But I'm starting to get some good ideas about how I might use it.
You sure?
You sure about that?
Yeah. Same as it was with Alt.
Wasn't even about guilt, that. Just some fucking sense of personal discomfort.
Know the weirdest thing, though?
Ahhh, horseshit…
Callin' me a liar?!
I'm sayin' it was hotter'n Satan's ass crack down in Salvador... People saw all kinds of crap.
No division, no unit, off the books... Appeared outta nowhere, then disappeared into the jungle. Jus' like that – ghosts.
What?
The way they moved, behaved... Almost like they was one person.
OK, guess I'ma go back to work.
We reserve the right to refuse service to anyone – yeah, good rule.
You really th-- Fuck!
Since when are my professional choices any of your fucking business?!
Got a name at the tip of your tongue, I know – Adam Smasher.
So, yes. But way later. You were gone, and I'd stopped dressing in mourning.
No room for sentimentality in the biz, Johnny. Smasher, me – we worked for the same people.
Does it stink like fresh shit? Yes. Did I have a choice? I did. Do I regret it...?
That what you wanted to hear?
Very much so.
If that's the case, do we talk about the future...? I know you, came here for a reason.
